					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So a note-on in an NES game might be delayed by 10 milliseconds. Big whoop. If your song's tempo doesn't divide easily into 901.5 BPM (NTSC) or 750 BPM (PAL), the note-ons will be jittered anyway. Or apart from the NES, if you have a live musician, how long might his notes get delayed? Music is <em>supposed</em> to sound slightly out of sync. Drum-machine precision is mostly an affectation of the past three decades.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

